Peak check

Sanne

27/01/2020

Generate datasets

Set variables

N <- 1000 # Sample size
p <- 1000 # Number of X variables
q <- 7 # Number of Y variables
K <- 50 # Number of bootstrapping iterations
r <- 3 # Number of joint components
rx <- 3 # Number of specific components of X
ry <- 4 # Number of specific components of Y

Generate parameters

params <- PO2PLS:::generate_params(p, q, r, rx, ry, type = "unit")

# Change parameters for different datasets
# Dataset 3: Joint component in one spot
params3 <- params
params3$W[c(1:610, 651:p)] <- rep(0.01, (p-40))
params3$W[611:650, 1] <- params3$W[611:650, 1]*3
params3$W[, -1] <- matrix(rep(0.01, (r-1)*p), ncol = (r-1))
params3$C[1:6, 1] <- rep(0.01, 6)
params3$C[, 2:3] <- matrix(rep(0.01, (r-1)*q), ncol = (r-1))

# Dataset 4: Peaks with average joint component
params4 <- params

# Dataset 5: Joint component in peak
params5 <- params
params5$W[241:280, 2] <-params5$W[241:280, 1]*2 
params5$W[611:650, 1] <- params5$W[611:650, 1]*3

# Peak check: peaks between 240-280 and 520-560
# Create new variable, store mean and variance
params3_p <- params3
params4_p <- params4
params5_p <- params5

# Parameters sorted from high to low, so sample to mix
for(i in 1:rx){
  params3_p$Wo[,i] <- params3_p$Wo[sample.int(N, N), i]
  params4_p$Wo[,i] <- params4_p$Wo[sample.int(N, N), i]
  params5_p$Wo[,i] <- params5_p$Wo[sample.int(N, N), i]
}

# Create peaks in both datasets, with varying peak height
params_list <- list(params3_p, params4_p, params5_p)
for(i in 1:length(params_list)){
  params_list[[i]]$Wo[241:280, 1] <- rnorm(40, mean=mean(params_list[[i]]$Wo[241:280, 1]), 
                                  sd=sd(params_list[[i]]$Wo[241:280, 1])*10)
  params_list[[i]]$Wo[521:560, 1] <- rnorm(40, mean=mean(params_list[[i]]$Wo[521:560, 1]), 
                                    sd=sd(params_list[[i]]$Wo[521:560, 1])*3)
  params_list[[i]]$Wo[431:470, 2] <- rnorm(40, mean=mean(params_list[[i]]$Wo[431:470, 1]), 
                                   sd=sd(params_list[[i]]$Wo[431:470, 2])*7)
  params_list[[i]]$Wo[841:880, 3] <- rnorm(40, mean=mean(params_list[[i]]$Wo[841:880, 1]), 
                                    sd=sd(params_list[[i]]$Wo[841:880, 3])*4)
}

Create datasets

data_list <- list('One joint component' = NA, 'Average joint component' = NA, 
                  "Specific and joint component" = NA)
x_list <- list(x3 = NA, x4 = NA, x5 = NA)
y_list <- list(y3 = NA, y4 = NA, y5 = NA)
for(i in 1: length(data_list)){
  data_list[[i]] <- PO2PLS:::generate_data(100, params_list[[i]])
  x_list[[i]] <- data_list[[i]][,1:1000]
  y_list[[i]] <- data_list[[i]][,1001:1007]
}

Run PO2PLS

Res_list <- list(res3 = NA, res4 = NA, res5 = NA)

for(i in 1:length(Res_list)){
  Res_list[[i]] <- PO2PLS(x_list[[i]], y_list[[i]], r, rx, ry, 
                          init_param = params_list[[i]], steps = 5000)
}

Results

Joint components

for (i in 1:r){
  for(j in 1:length(Res_list)){
    plot(Res_list[[j]]$params$W[,i], main = paste(names(data_list)[j], "\n Joint component", i))
  }
}

Orthogonal components

for (i in 1:r){
  for(j in 1:length(Res_list)){
    plot(svd(x_list[[j]],0,3)$v[,i], main = paste(names(data_list)[j], "\n SVD", i))
    plot(Res_list[[j]]$params$Wo[,i], 
         main = paste(names(data_list)[j], "\n Specific component", i))
  }
}
